answers.answer: That is called a false low...  your body is used to high BG so 90 feels low.  your body will get used to lower numbers and the "low feeling" will go away.
Thanks! That's so depressing :-( but I'm new to the diabetes game so learning all this new stuff day by day.

question: Does anyone get shaky or dizzy when their blood sugar levels are 90 and lower? I know 70 or lower is when your blood sugar is low but I feel the symptoms at 90...
title: Below 90 blood sugar levels?
